title: DIARY-Emerging Markets Economic Events to Oct 29
text:
Oct 16 (Reuters) -

Government debt auctions
Political and general news events
Index of all diaries
Guide to economic indicators
** This Diary is filed daily *** FRIDAY, OCTOBER 16 MILAN, Italy - Italian Economy Minister Pier Carlo Padoan, European Bank for Reconstruction and Development President Suma Chakrabarti and World Bank Director General Mulyani Indrawati speak at the Finance for Food conference in Milan. PRETORIA - South African Reserve Bank Governor Lesetja Kganyago speaks at 'Open Mic" session with media - 1530 GMT. LIMA - Central bank of Peru announces interest rate decision - 2300 GMT. ACCRA - World Bank president Jim Yong Kim visits Ghana to launch a report on ending extreme poverty. TUESDAY, OCTOBER 20 PRAGUE - Czech National Bank board member Pavel Rezabek to speak in Brno CNB subdivision - 0800 GMT. BUDAPEST - Central Bank of Hungary rate-setting meeting. BRASILIA - Central Bank of Brazil holds Monetary Policy Committee Meeting (to Oct. 21). WARSAW - National Bank of Poland holds Monetary Policy Council meeting (Interest rate announcement not expected). KAMPALA - Central bank of Uganda interest rate decision - 1000 GMT. WEDNESDAY, OCTOBER 21 WINDHOEK - Central bank of Namibia holds Monetary Policy Meeting - 1000 GMT. BRASILIA - Central bank of Brazil announces interest rate decision - 2100 GMT. CAPE TOWN - South African Finance Minister Nhlanhla Nene presents his first medium-term budget policy statement to parliament, with the Treasury's latest budget deficit and economic growth projections for the next three years - 1300 GMT. ANKARA - Central Bank of Turkey monetary policy meeting - 1100 GMT. THURSDAY, OCTOBER 22 STELLENBOSCH, South Africa - South African Reserve Bank Governor Lesetja Kganyago speaks at an economic conference - 0640 GMT. JAKARTA - World Bank issues its quarterly economic review for Indonesia - 0200 GMT. FRIDAY, OCTOBER 23 PARIS - Czech National Bank board member Kamil Janacek to attend a conference on "Securitisation: the way forward?". SUNDAY, OCTOBER 25 ABU DHABI, United Arab Emirates - Summit on the Global Agenda 2015 (to Oct. 27). MONDAY, OCTOBER 26 JERUSALEM - Bank of Israel announces interest rate decision - 1430 GMT. WEDNESDAY, OCTOBER 28 ANKARA - Central bank of Turkey releases quarterly inflation report - 0800 GMT. ANKARA - Central bank of Turkey to publish the minutes of October policy meeting - 1200 GMT.
THURSDAY, OCTOBER 29 LONDON - UK finance minister George Osborne meets Brazilian finance minister Joaquim Levy as a part of UK-Brazil Economic and Financial Dialogue.
